  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And there came in two men, children of Belial, and sat before him,.... Which position showed that they were his accusers, and had a charge against him; it being usual for the accusers and accused to be set face to face, as it was the manner of the Romans in later times, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 25:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Josephus says (d) there were \"three\" men to accuse him; but the Targum, and all the ancient versions, have only \"two\": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the men of Belial witnessed against him, even against Naboth, in the presence of the people; both before the judges of the court, and before all the people that filled it, who came to hear the trial; so bold and impudent were they: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying, Naboth did blaspheme God and the king; or \"bless\", an euphemism; the phrase of cursing God being shocking to the ear, and therefore such a word is used to express it, see Job 1:5, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "saying, Naboth did blaspheme God and the king; or \"bless\", an euphemism; the phrase of cursing God being shocking to the ear, and therefore such a word is used to express it, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Job 1:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "then they carried him forth out of the city; without any further process of examining witnesses, and of hearing what the accused had to say in his defence; but immediately they carried him out of court, and out of the city, to put him to death, malefactors being executed always without the city: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and stoned him with stones, that he died; which was the death blasphemers were put to, Leviticus 24:14, of the manner of which; see Gill on Acts 7:58, it seems from 2 Kings 9:26, that his sons were stoned with him. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and stoned him with stones, that he died; which was the death blasphemers were put to, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 24:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", of the manner of which; see Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 7:58",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", it seems from ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Kings 9:26",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", that his sons were stoned with him. ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(d) Antiqu. l. 3. c. 13. sect. 8. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(d) Antiqu. l. 3. c. 13. sect. 8. ",
            "children": []
