          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "did blaspheme",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] R.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "did curse",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The word is the same as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 21:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". But a different word is used for ‘blaspheme’ in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 24:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "they carried him forth out of the city",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] This explains what is meant by ‘carry him out’ in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 21:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The place of execution was to be outside the walls, according to the legal ordinance (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 24:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), ‘Bring forth him that hath cursed without the camp … and let all the congregation stone him.’ From this we see that this enactment was before the Exile.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
