      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "yesternight",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Stanley suggests that the trial took place by night. But the word is often used in the wider sense of \"yesterday\" (Gesenius)] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "two men, children of Belial, and sat before him: and the men of Belial witnessed against him, even against Naboth, in the presence of the people",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [The whole congregation was interested in a charge of blasphemy. If unpunished, the guilt rested on the congregation. Hence the provision of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 24:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". By the imposition of hands they testified that the guilt of the blasphemer thenceforth rested upon his own head], ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "saying, Naboth did blaspheme God and the king. Then they carried him forth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [Heb. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "made him to go forth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
